items.text: My favorite little cafe in the middle of the market. Brilliant sandwiches, excellent coffee, and other wonderful dishes.  Fridays are especially packed, thanks to the special Friday dishes.

small place, dark sometimes with the great and simple food. Friday mornings expect the waiting line outside. Very reasonable prices.

venue.description: Dizengoff Center is a shopping mall at the intersection of Dizengoff Street and King George Street in Tel Aviv. The mall is named for Meir Dizengoff, the first mayor of Tel Aviv.

items.text: On Tuesdays there a food court here, with lots of different home-made and otherwise great food.
The only shopping mall that allow dogs inside!

The first mall in Israel, ever, and it remains unique. Usual brands alongside shops you won't see anywhere else. Cinemas, books, music, clothes, gadgets, a pool and an indoor food market every Friday.
a great place to escape the heat and humidity
Tel Aviv's first and truly *central* shopping mall. Great for clothes, book browsing and gift shopping. Less great for food although Fridays host a super busy food market.
The concourse in a nice natural snaily path. All big brands (McDo, Zara, Mac, Nike, Crocs,...) are there. Cheap and cute clothes at Fox.
Disk Center is probably the cheapest (and legal) record store in Tel Aviv
Close your eyes and listen the real balagan!
